Mix LaChoy Teriyaki and soy sauce, rice wine, oil, ginger, garlic, chili oil, and sesame oil in a medium bowl; add sirloin. Marinade sirloin cubes in up to 3 hours or, over night in the refrigerator. (Use reserved marinade for basting.) Thread mushrooms, beef, peppers and pineapple on skewer alternately. Grill skewers over medium hot fire on rack 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly charred. Baste frequently with reserved marinade; turn frequently.